.TH CPIP 1 "2026-07-23" "CPIP v5.0.5" "Coffee Pot Internet Protocol"
.SH NAME
cpip \- command-line client for the Coffee Pot Internet Protocol
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cpip
[\fBtui\fR|\fBstatus\fR|\fBbrew\fR|\fBpour\fR|\fBwhen\fR|\fBinfo\fR|\fBconfig\fR|\fBstats\fR|\fBversion\fR|\fBwhoami\fR|\fB418\fR|\fBadditions\fR|\fBmesh\fR|\fBitf\fR|\fBcovert\fR|\fBecc\fR|\fBdeaddrop\fR|\fBdefense\fR|\fBidentity\fR|\fBdns\fR|\fBgroups\fR|\fBsync\fR|\fBcluster\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
cpip communicates with a running CPIP/HTCPCP server. It implements RFC 2324
(Hyper Text Coffee Pot Control Protocol) and RFC 7168 (HTCPCP-TEA), plus the
CPIP mesh extension for peer-to-peer messaging, covert channels, E2EE, and
multi-transport routing.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B tui [\fIhost\fR] [\fIport\fR]
Launch the Terminal UI (OpenTUI). Default: localhost:4180.
.TP
.B status
Show server status.
.TP
.B brew \fIbeverage\fR [\fIadditions\fR]
Start brewing. Beverage: coffee or tea. Additions: comma-separated
name;variety=value pairs (e.g. milk;variety=whole, sugar;variety=honey).
.TP
.B pour \fIbeverage\fR [\fIadditions\fR]
Alias for brew.
.TP
.B when
Stop pouring.
.TP
.B info
Pot metadata (PROPFIND).
.TP
.B config
Show full node configuration (JSON).
.TP
.B stats
Show all status at a glance (node, mesh, sat, radio, mobile).
.TP
.B version
Show server version.
.TP
.B whoami
Show local node identity (POT_ID, address, hostname, device).
.TP
.B 418
Trigger HTTP 418 by brewing coffee on a teapot.
.TP
.B 418-alcohol
Trigger HTTP 418 by brewing alcohol on a teapot.
.TP
.B additions
List supported addition types.
.TP
.B mesh status
Mesh network status.
.TP
.B mesh peers
List mesh peers.
.TP
.B mesh inbox
Read received messages.
.TP
.B mesh send \fIpot\fR \fImessage\fR
Send E2EE message to a peer.
.TP
.B mesh broadcast \fImessage\fR
Broadcast to all peers.
.TP
.B mesh send-raw \fIpot\fR \fImessage\fR
Send a raw (unencrypted) message to a peer (debugging).
.TP
.B mesh scan
Scan for peers on the network.
.TP
.B mesh routes
Show routing table.
.TP
.B mesh sat
Satellite mesh status.
.TP
.B mesh radio
Radio / LoRa transport status.
.TP
.B mesh mobile
Mobile broadband transport status.
.TP
.B mesh queued
Show store-and-forward queue.
.TP
.B itf status
Full defense posture (418, stealth, blacklist).
.TP
.B itf blacklist
List blacklisted IP addresses.
.TP
.B itf whitelist \fIaddr\fR
Remove an address from the blacklist.
.TP
.B itf clear
Clear the entire blacklist.
.TP
.B itf stealth
Show stealth and port-hopping status.
.TP
.B itf probe \fIaddr\fR
Check if an address is blacklisted.
.TP
.B covert encode \fImessage\fR [\fIdst\fR]
Encode a message into an Accept-Additions header.
.TP
.B covert decode \fIheader\fR
Decode a message from an Accept-Additions header.
.TP
.B covert brew \fImessage\fR [\fIdst\fR]
Brew with a hidden covert message.
.TP
.B covert status
Show covert channel status.
.TP
.B ecc status
ECC engine and address book status.
.TP
.B ecc address
Show this node's ECC address.
.TP
.B ecc book
List address book entries.
.TP
.B ecc resolve \fIaddr\fR
Resolve an ECC address to a POT_ID.
.TP
.B deaddrop list
List dead-drop messages held by this node.
.TP
.B deaddrop claim \fIid\fR
Claim a dead-drop message.
.TP
.B defense status
Show the full ITF defense posture (alias for \fBitf status\fR).
.TP
.B identity
List all known identities.
.TP
.B identity publish
Publish this node's identity to the mesh.
.TP
.B identity vouch \fIpot_id\fR [\fIlevel\fR]
Vouch for a peer (2=marginal, 3=full).
.TP
.B identity graph
Show the trust graph.
.TP
.B dns register \fIname\fR
Register a .pot DNS name.
.TP
.B dns resolve \fIname\fR
Resolve a name to a pot_id.
.TP
.B dns list
List all registered names.
.TP
.B groups create \fIname\fR
Create a new E2EE group chat.
.TP
.B groups send \fIgroup_id\fR \fImessage\fR
Send an encrypted message to a group.
.TP
.B groups join \fIgroup_id\fR
Join a group.
.TP
.B groups history \fIgroup_id\fR
View group message history.
.TP
.B sync send \fIchannel\fR \fImessage\fR
Send an offline-sync message.
.TP
.B sync pending
Show pending undelivered messages.
.TP
.B sync request \fIpot_id\fR
Request sync from a mesh peer.
.TP
.B cluster start [\fIn\fR]
Start an n-node mesh cluster for testing.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B CPIP_HOST
Server hostname (default: localhost).
.TP
.B CPIP_PORT
Server port (default: 4180).
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Brew tea with milk
.B cpip brew tea "milk;variety=whole"
.TP
Send a mesh message
.B cpip mesh send a1b2c3d4 "Hello"
.TP
Check defense posture
.B cpip itf status
.TP
Encode a covert message
.B cpip covert encode "secret data"
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/local/bin/cpip
CLI client.
.SH BUGS
Classical cryptography (AES-256-GCM, ECDSA/ECDH P-256, HKDF/HMAC-SHA256) is
FIPS-compliant via the \fBcryptography\fR library. 1nf1D3L's Kyber (ML-KEM-768
variant with η=3) is NOT FIPS 203 validated — it is intended for research,
red-teaming, and coffee-protocol use cases, not FIPS-required deployments.
CPIP does not implement RSA-KEM; the hybrid KEM is ECDH P-256 + Kyber.
